---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import { APP_URL, href, t } from '../../i18n/ui';

const tr = t('en');
---

<Base
  lang="en"
  routeKey="method"
  title="About & method — Sereno"
  description="Why Sereno is manual, local, and free: the manifesto of a budgeting app that refuses anxiety and bank syncing."
>
  <section class="hero-about section-soft">
    <div class="wrap about-grid">
      <div>
        <span class="lbl">About</span>
        <h1>A budgeting app built to calm, not to rush.</h1>
        <p>
          Sereno is an independent project. No marketing team, no ad model, no
          hidden paid plan. Just an app that answers one precise anxiety: not
          knowing where the money goes.
        </p>
      </div>
      <img src="/illustrations/local-first.svg" alt="" width="220" height="180" class="about-illo" />
    </div>
  </section>

  <article class="section">
    <div class="wrap prose">
      <span class="lbl">The manifesto</span>
      <h2>Manual, on purpose.</h2>

      <p>
        Every budgeting app promises the same thing: “connect your bank, we’ll
        handle the rest.” Sereno bets the opposite — by design, not as a
        missing feature.
      </p>

      <h2>Anxiety doesn’t come from lack of money</h2>
      <p>
        It comes from not knowing. The overdraft you discover too late, the
        “where did my paycheck go?” on the 20th, the banking app you dread
        opening. The information existed — somewhere in an automatic feed
        nobody looks at.
      </p>
      <p>
        Full automation has a blind spot: what you don’t do yourself, you don’t
        feel. A charge imported silently at 3 a.m. teaches you nothing. The
        same expense logged by you, in five seconds, leaves a trace — in the
        app and in your head.
      </p>

      <h2>Five seconds that change your relationship with money</h2>
      <p>
        Logging a purchase by hand is short. But in those five seconds you know
        what you just spent, you choose its category, you watch it join the
        month. That repeated micro-gesture does what no algorithm can do for
        you: it puts you back in charge.
      </p>
      <blockquote>
        Manual entry isn’t the price of using Sereno. It’s the treatment.
      </blockquote>

      <h2>What Sereno does so it sticks</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>The gesture is reduced to essentials.</strong> Amount,
          category, saved. Templates for what comes back often, recurring rules
          for what is truly mechanical (rent, subscriptions).
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>The reward is immediate.</strong> Every entry feeds the
          dashboard and statistics. You literally watch your money take shape.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>No punishment.</strong> An exceeded budget shows in coral,
          with a calm statement. Missing three days of logging erases nothing,
          breaks no “streak.” You pick up again — that’s it.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Free, no trap</h2>
      <p>
        Everything is free forever — guest mode and sync account. No quotas, no
        AI, no Plus plan. If you want to support the project, it’s voluntary: a
        coffee, a sandwich, a boost via the
        <a href={href('en', 'support')}>Support page</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>What that implies — honestly</h2>
      <p>
        Sereno won’t suit everyone. If you want an aggregator that categorizes
        three bank accounts without lifting a finger, excellent apps exist for
        that. Sereno is for people who already tried — and noticed that watching
        imported lines scroll by never changed how they spend.
      </p>

      <hr />

      <p>
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href={APP_URL} aria-label={tr('cta.openApp.aria')}>
          {tr('cta.openApp')}
        </a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>

<style>
  .hero-about {
    padding: 72px 0 56px;
  }

  .about-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: 32px;
    align-items: center;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  }

  .about-grid h1 {
    font-size: clamp(30px, 5vw, 42px);
    margin: 14px 0 16px;
  }

  .about-grid p {
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    font-size: 18px;
    max-width: 42ch;
  }

  .about-illo {
    width: min(100%, 240px);
    height: auto;
    justify-self: start;
  }

  @media (min-width: 800px) {
    .about-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1.4fr 0.6fr;
    }

    .about-illo {
      justify-self: end;
    }
  }

  .prose .lbl {
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
</style>
